des:
You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off or dim the light. There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust you home light - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo. 

After connecting Alexa to your Spectrum SMART products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "Spectrum SMART" app in android or ios app market;
(2). Register one Spectrum SMART account in our "Spectrum SMART" app;
(3). You need to have some Spectrum SMART devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our Spectrum SMART app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "Spectrum SMART" skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android,ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "Spectrum SMART" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "Spectrum SMART", and you'll be navigated to Spectrum SMART login page;
(9). Input your Spectrum SMART account username and password, you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished. 

You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on kitchen light"
“Alexa, turn off kitchen light"
“Alexa, dim livingroom light"
“Alexa, brighten livingroom light"
“Alexa, set the livingroom light to 20 percent"
“Alexa, set bedroom light to Blue"

Currently this skill supports products:
smart switch,
smart socket, 
smart bulb....
